text: An extremely cozy cafe, especially on the higher floors! Calming music and a soothing ambience. The salt coffee is also good and is not just a cup full of ice (this isn't as common as it should be). However, you may want to add another shot to the drink if you prefer your drink stronger.

Nice coffee place, expensive but worth the price for the atmosphere and quality of coffee. There’s three stories and aircon was good, you can get out of the hot weather here. The Pandan lotus tea was amazing, definitely worth a try. Salt coffee was delicious too.

A super nice coffee place to chill out and its 3 storey tall. The top floor seems like allow smoking. Too bad the egg coffee sold out when we reached after dinner. So we drunk the traditional drip coffee. Great place to unwind after a hectic or bz day! There are these book in Vietnamese in the cafe altho i dont understand it but the prologue is in english is very inspirational written by founder of the cafe itself.
Tasteful coffee! Coconut coffee is a must try! Most of the staff is very welcome to the tourists
So many different coffees to choose from! Great service and delicious coffee. Main/ground floor plus two other floors! Lots of space and great view of the streets. Will definitely come again!

Good chill out spot in the mist of the city traffic. Don't let the ground floor fool you . There are 3 levels of cafe seating area upstairs. For most folks , it just look like a shop that sell beans and take away , however the upper deck has beautiful bay windows for you to watch the world goes by. Not to crowded at times. Staff serve coffee right up to which ever floor you are seating. Music is fine and coffee are great .
This was one of the best coffee shop experiences I've had. First, I got to experience an exotic coffee. Second, the atmosphere and view were nice. Last, the staff had the best attitudes and service.

Wonderful coffee connoisseur! Beans are intense and robust, not the usual Asian sour fruit but more towards the Italian strong coffee flavour, with hint of chocolate! There’s a range of coffee flavours to choose from. The Legend - drip coffee with or without condense milk (for the man or those who like intense taste) coconut coffee - sweet Pandan leaf smell & taste in ice blended, paired wonderfully with the strong coffee. Motherland coffee - sweet with fresh GINGER flavour & CREME! This is really an interesting pairing that I’ve not tried before in my life! 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻 If you’re a coffee lover, just sit in here and enjoy, let time pass ❤️❤️❤️
It's a good and comfortable place plus the staff are very friendly.
Waited 30 mins for a cup of coffee and was cold when it arrived. Customer service is terrible and rude. Nice place though pity they don't care about their customers.

Cute interior. Came here and it was not busy. However the young lady was of no help helping me find luwak coffee. Instead I got the egg coffe and it was presented nicely and the egg made the coffee creamy and velvety.

Very spacious building with multiple floors to choose from, very comfy with free flow water. Got the special drip coffee, was really delicious! For those as clueless as me, the steps is to wait for water to be done dripping, mix milk, then mix with ice. Takes about 20-30min for it to fully drip
When I don't have access to my machine their cappuccino with hazelnut is my go to. Picked up half a dozen boxes as it's difficult or overpriced in Australia. One day I'll come back to eat here.

Had high hopes based on recommendations and reviews but was a bit disappointed. Let’s start with the good stuff though, the egg coffee is fantastic. I’d highly recommend it. Unfortunately the food is a big let down. My wife’s rice came out cold and the bread I was given was about as dry as a desert. We were also only given 1 set of cutlery to share. Overall, if you’re just stopping for coffee, go for it. But if not, then look elsewhere.
I really like the coffee, suite with my taste and the ambience is cozy and comfortable
Chic. Delicious. Good coffee. Nice spots. Calm ambience. Nice view. Love the spot!!

Great layout of cafe with multiple floors. We had the coconut coffee and it was delicious. Nice presentation. Took about q5 minutes or so. Service a bit slow. Smoking room on top floor has smell of cigarettes on floor 2 as well. Should not allow smoking upstairs indoors. Little pricey for the service levels 55k for coffee. Free wifi. Coffee is good though.
Cute and friendly waitresses and a good place to bum. Had the grilled pork rice, meat is on the tough side but like the generous servings of veg in the soup. Overall a place I will revisit again.
Very good coffee. The cashier was able to speak simple English which makes ordering easier. He also recommended some drinks for us.
First coffee in HCM. it was so nice. The staff also recommend what kind of coffees are suitable for me too
Good coffee Good prices Nice staff Copy spot Good for a break and relax for a bit
Coffee is tasty and you can buy beans too. Not many options to eat here including desserts and sweets. Staff is awful. The atmosphere is really great on 1st floor, nice place to hangout.

The legend coffee wasn't great considering the price relative to other drip coffee with the phin filter you can get around the city. From the older reviews on google, I had mistaken the egg coffee as the tiramisu. If you're from the west, the tiramisu lacks a lot of what you're accustomed to, you should avoid it.

Trung nguyen legend iced coffee 170k vnd. Banh mi beef stew 79k. Was served the beef stew and didn’t get the coffee until 15 minutes later.. just some timing issues. Not sure why the coffee comes out so late. The banh mi beef stew was excellent. The coffee was great but with condensed milk every coffee will taste good so i’d probably try the black coffee next time to see how legendary it is. Top floor is smoking.. kind of a waste of a floor. It was extremely busy but the smoking floor was empty.

Great spot to get some coffee, drinks and foods for business or pleasure. Place is clean and decor is nice. In addition, it not as nosy as their competitors (highland coffee), which is a plus. Great place to do work if necessary.
Good place with great view facing traffic junctions at 2nd floor. Banh mi is good. Banana crepes is recommended. Affordable price.

I have really loved this cafe before corona. But after corona, many things changed. They removes espresso bar on 2nd floor. Old expert staffs have left and young rookie staffs can not make special coffee menu. They changed many delicious coffee menu. Nowadays, this cafe is just normal other branches trung nguyen cafe. ------------------------------------------- Tastes really good Trung is center(中), Nguyen is, not pretty sure but, I guess, one of these...原 or 元. So, trung nguyen is a famous chinese place name '中(center)原(big branch, origin)' . This word means 'middle of china' or 'heart of china'. Anyway there are many coffees, But I strongly recommend two coffees in this shop. The First one is 'Caphe L'amour' This is a french word, coffee of love. And the other one is 'legend coffee' This one is a 'weazle coffee'. Maybe if you are coffee mania You knew it. This weazle coffee is really expensive and dam so good. One cup of natural weazle coffee costs around 50 dollars. But this legend coffee is not natural. It is a farm weazle. But comparing to original, this is 95% similar. And one thing more, The most expensive coffee in the world is an 'Elephant coffee' in Anatara resort & hotel in theThailand. One cup of it costs almost 4times more than natural weazle, 200$.

Great quiet cafe with aircon. 2nd floor has nicest room. Coffee is great. I can recommend the 'sang tao number 4' coffee. Lovely rich flavour. Trung Nguyen Legend has cafes across the country in cities and larger towns. My fav coffee brand in Vietnam.
Wifi is quite fast. Coffee is good.
Nice ambience with very friendly staff. Coffee normal. Nothing fantastic. It's on the first floor. Great view of the street scenes and its surrounding below.

Vietnam has by far the best coffee I have ever had! Trung Nguyen Cafe Legend chain Cafe's are simply amazing, and very highly recommend! The Motherland Iced Coffee blew my mind, has a hint of ginger, with many other complex and amazing flavors, must try!!! As did the Green Tea Latte with jelly, a matcha floral and honey essence with square coffee jellies and so many other complex flavors, wow!!! A great chain cafe to experience some Vietnamese flavors! p.s. It is noted there is also a cinnamon coffee that is amazing if you are in the mood, and can ask the barista if you are inclined!
Nice place, free wifi, v nice Vietnamese coffee and place to get Fresh hi end coffee. A place I will come for meetings and chill out
Great coffee, location and ambient. Staff was very friendly. 1st and 2nd floor are smoking the third is not. Good A/C and nice view from the windows. The coffee was quite expensive.
Do not buy coffee beans from here they scam you they give you old coffee what's out of date. Pay good price get bad coffee

It was very spacious and relaxing after a hectic shopping and exploration around the city. And at times there are discounts for the products so do check with the staff there to get a good price for legit products.
The service is sucks, no smile, correct customer, bad attitude. I will not come here 2nd time

While this is a highly famous coffee chain, I don’t appreciate the coffee as much as the local stores. We also order the legend coffee which is the weasel coffee that cost us 170,000. It’s quite smooth and nice. The place is nicely decor and nice to chill
Great selection of aromatic coffes and desserts. Elegant interior. Good for a break from the heat and street noise.
Nice cafe over three floors (last floor is for smokers). They also have a small shop on the street level where the coffee is cheaper and better than in any tourist shop.
Cafe is multiple storeys. Coconut coffee is my favourite order here. Nice, clean, air-conditioned. Toilets available on two floors.
A more refined Vietnamese cafe experience. Great ambience with plenty of seats. There are sandwiches and rice. Limited cakes or rather mousse options. Friendly staff.
Great coffee with a wide variety of options and flavors. Food was also very good. Seating near the window on the second level makes for fun people watching and city happenings
Trung Nguyen Legend Coffee. Expensive! But this is the legend. Nice cacao aroma, deep rich taste. You should come here if you like coffee and visited Hồ Chí Minh!
Great coffee with a great view of the intersection :) we ordered the drip coffee with ice. Not so crowded.
Nice place, unique and delicious coffee. You can not find that taste in other country. Only in vietnam.
The coffee is always good. But place is a bit small
Got a passion fruit smoothie for 65,000 VND. Bathroom, outlets (bring your own charger), free WiFi, and AC! Lots of room to sit and relax. Nice calming music in the background.
Legendary cafe in the middle of everything. Great pick me up every morning I was there. Strong af coffee. Careful!

The taste is good. But I didn't get any recommendations or from bartender, like at least they have to asked that I would like cold or hot or else. Would be much better if they asked and consult more so customer can have best experience from the staff with good taste of coffee.
Excellent coffee very nice yummy food at reasonable price. Will come back and would recommend
Legendary Vietnam coffee. Dark, sweet and tasty! Relaxing vibe. (You must try motherland coffee - ginger coffee)
Tried their egg coffee.. and it was so good!

Firstly , the staff didn’t greet me as I am Vietnamese but they greet a foreigner man when he just entered the door. I didn’t know there is discrimination among Vietnamese. Secondly you have to to upstairs to have breakfast. I am an elderly and got knee problems. I saw a table with two chairs near the counter and when I asked the staff to sit there but he refused because it is only for people who bought take away. Thirdly, they served me with old bread roll since I ordered meat ball with bread roll. I am very disappointed and upset.

Too expensive for its taste. We had a coffee for 280,000 vnd that already has 2 full meal. Just overhyped. We also asked the waitress if they would recommend anything ASIDE from the legend coffee but they just said “legend” and i asked twice lol. Anyway just visit Cong Ca Phe and Little Hanoi Egg Coffee if you want cheaper and better tasting food.
Good coffee. The staff is not super friendly though.
Good place to chill and people watch. Especially those seats by the window on second n third level.
Honestly, Trung Nguyen coffee is the best :). Good place at crossroad to see people walking around the street

Be careful, you can end up with a 7€ euro coffee… So definitely not worthy. In HCMC you can find excellent coffee at a normal price everywhere! While I asked for a normal black hot coffee, the waitress played like she didn’t understand and made me take the “Legend signature coffee” at 170000 VD which I did not want. I explained it three times but nothing to do about it…
We got a yellow drink when we came which we felt tasted more like water with smoke?? Service is great though and it is a very cozy place to sit with friends and talk while drinking coffee

Avocado smoothie was poorly made, had a feeling we were eating avocado flavored ice. We asked the stuff to blend it again and they were not happy with our request. Also, prices are two times average price in this area and portions and quality are below average.

Its ok place for the guys love peace space.evething is very good include coffe, drink and food except to the price.its quite expensive but can be acceptable. Order for food is nightmare, veryyyyyy longgggg.

The shot was taken at the 2nd storey of Trung Nguyen Cafe Legend. Watching the busyness of the street activities whilst dispelling the concerns of the world over an aromatic cuppe of 'Old Motherland'.
one of choice for budget traveler to find coffee gift to bring home.
It's too pricey here though the cafe are beautifully designed. Coffee is nice but I prefer other brand.
It is expensive, but good. I mean the espresso and stuff, but you can buy caffee beans for about 180k - 330k per kilogram. These are almost the average price for coffee
One of the best coffee brands in town. Very nice location with good view from the second floor
Coffee was amazing, very nice space to relax after long walk and great street views !
A top branded coffee shop in Vietnam
Nice staff, good coffee. I tried the signature, pricey but good. I wish there was a little more though, for the price.
Nice decorations coffee shop near Ben Thanh Market. Tasty and friendly staffs
Tried the Sang Tao 5 : Ice Coffee with Milk.. it taste so good
Second floor is excellent work place if you need some quiet hours with your notebook, a power point, and wireless. For coffee, don't come here. The taste is average, and the service non-existent.

The service of this Trung Nguyen cafe is so inferior that we had to wait for more than 15 minutes before our coffee was served. Other customers were waiting impatiently as well. The seating area is on the second floor with narrow staircase. I will not return to this cafe again.
Service very slowly …. And no body take care clean table so bad
Nice coffee shop with many creative drinks.

Don't waste your time coming on over here it's expensive coffee and self-service from ordering yourself from.. the register and self-serve of everything this is the high price of coffee in Saigon and. it tastes okay you can get better.. coffee in plenty of places in Saigon and you can get a better service than this place who want to plays expensive coffee in Self Service when you come to Saigon you want people 2 serve you. don't want to be self service. if there is a. Minus stars I would give this place a negative Stars personally I would stay away from this place.. and the staff was very rude
Had lunch here. Lunch was good. Fried rice was nice and coffee was good
If you’re in a morning rush, definitely not for you.

The 3 floors to this cafe and big lookout windows make it great for sipping a coffee and looking over this huge city. More expensive than the average cafe however the coffee is worth the extra. They serve smoothies and fresh juices too.

You pay for quality here, so don’t be taken aback by their prices. I wasn’t prepared to pay their higher end coffee prices as in my opinion if you’re adding sweetened condensed milk to coffee you’re probably destroying any quality notes you’d otherwise taste. If you need a caffeine fix stick to a cheaper cafe or 7/11 but if you want to relax with a view, taste some local coffee and maybe even head to the fourth floor for a cigarette, this is your place.
A very slow turnaround of clean glasses for complimentary self served iced tea/water. Otherwise a fairly good service amid an extended menu of premium coffees and soft drinks.
Ridiculously slow service. Waited 15+ minutes for a simple cappuccino. It’s been almost 40 minutes and no desert. Coffee is overpriced for average quality.

Local place trying to make good. Lousy cheap coffee marked up higher pricing, smoking allowed inside aircon floor, untrained staffs providing poor services. Definitely not a place to visit for foreigners unless you are engaging in biz discussions with locals.

Gorgeous view, near distant to Ben Thanh market and Nguyen Hue street. The staffs are friendly and enthusiastic, and Trung Nguyen's coffee is one of the most prestigious and best quality coffee you will ever find in Viet Nam. I highly recommend any visitor to come and try out their coffee and atmospheric scenery.
Nice coffee shop in the middle of district 1 in Sai Gon very friendly and helpful staff. Prices are ok plenty of drinking options.

Amazing coffee! Nice quiet place with aircon. You can buy some coffee beans or ground coffee in the store on the ground floor or take a seat on the 2nd floor,order your coffee and just have relax with good city view.
nice smell coffee.

I visited this outlet when I first arrived in Ho Chi Minh City and I was recommended the Motherland coffee. It was the best coffee I have had in Vietnam! Before I end my trip om saturday, i wanted to have the same Motherland coffee again and so, I walked all the way to this outlet despite there are several other outlets along the way. As I was carrying many shopping bags, I wanted to have coffee on the ground floor but I was told this is not allowed. I climbed the stairs to the 3rd floor without much choice. I was told that the Motherland Coffee was not available as there is no more ginger. This is unbelievable! I was there around 2pm and Ben Thanh Market is just nearby. Oh well! I ordered a Matcha Latte that is good too. Ready to go, i went downstairs to make payment. To my horror, I saw 2 caucasians drinking on the ground floor. I approached the lady at the cashier and enquired why I was not allowed to drink here just now. She was shocked and fumbled to explain. I was told that there are no more seats upstairs! I recalled the table next to me was empty. Oh well! I guess it is just double standard. If the whole incident was due to unprofessional service by the staff, please educate the lady at the cashier with her hair bunned up.

At first it looks like a tourist trap, but the Viet Coffee is pretty decent! Just beware of their pricing strategy with different flowery sounding names for different coffee. Cost around 110k vnd for a coffee and a slice of cake (their matcha and tiramisu cake are not bad, although not the best)
Very nice environment and very nice dripping coffee and very good pricing also. Expected 3 times or more higher then any others cafe. Still worth try😂
Without doubt the best coffee in the world - like Starbucks chain but better. Creative energy coffees that provide a blend of so many flavours never had coffee like this anywhere else.
Absolutely best coffee!
Tried the most expensive coffee. All good. Atmosphere is great.

It's okay, first time we come here,inside is perfect with A/C,quiet, when we come upstairs have some customers but every body talk whispering, services is excellent. Perfect for romantic dating. Highly recommended

Coffee was good. Many branches in hcmc. Worth trying the coffee. Limited options for food, only banh mi and some dessert. The outlet I've been to, service level and staff attentiveness need to be improved.

To the coffee chain's management team: please turn off the slogan "coffee for happy and successful people", it is so ridiculous. Your differentiation lies in coffee special taste, special food from highland province, cutural actitives you've supported (e.g. Saturday coffee salon) and thousand of free books you give to customers. Your coffee has the string with intellectual, and intellectual never speaks louder than action. I used to love Trung Nguyen coffee until reading this stupid and arrogant slogan. Hope you should re-brand soon and take back the leading position in coffee retail shop.
Pretty typical for the chain. The coffee is great, but they serve artichoke tea, which I personally find totally gross. Nice environment. limited seating.
I'd say it's a must-visit while in HCMC. I've been here every day during my stay. What a coffee!
Very good taste high class of coffee especially for energy

Service is fine. However, we tried the number 3 and 8 (their best) and were underwhelmed, especially as the price was much more than at a local coffee shop. You should try the coffee in the shop before you buy any beans/grounds.

Serve great coffee. Nice comfortable place. Problem is their menu. The description of their coffee does not really tell you more of the coffee instead it sounded like they only wants you to buy their more expensive range.

Nice environment for coffee, although we were seated in the smoking section without being asked our preference. Ordered the banana crepes, they were delicious!

Nice environment, but I dont have impression about coffeee

original_text: 吃完好吃的越南麵包之後，想找個地方坐坐，發現附近就有一間中原咖啡，進店時感受到微微的、舒服的涼意，雖然看不太懂菜單，保守的選了 creative 4咖啡。 咖啡端上來時還可以看到咖啡正在緩緩低落，一邊欣賞店內設計，一邊等待咖啡滴完（雖然我最後沒耐心的直接倒入杯中開始品嚐就是了🤣），但入口時濃濃的口感，不像台灣咖啡常常會覺得淡淡的或是有水味，口感極佳，中間有層次的在嘴巴中展現不同的味道，最後以咖啡的苦味做為結尾，人生第一次體會到品嚐咖啡的經驗（驚豔）。 如果有來胡志明市強烈推薦，有許多連鎖店不用特地要找這一間。唯一的缺點：不知道回台灣怎麼喝咖啡😅😅。
text: After eating the delicious Vietnamese bread, I wanted to find a place to sit and found that there was a Zhongyuan Coffee nearby. I felt a slight and comfortable chill when I entered the store. Although I couldn’t understand the menu, I conservatively chose Creative 4 Coffee. . When the coffee was served, you could see that the coffee was slowly draining. While admiring the design of the store, you were waiting for the coffee to finish dripping (although I was impatient in the end and just poured it into the cup and started tasting it🤣), but the taste was strong when I entered it. , unlike Taiwanese coffee, which often tastes light or watery, it tastes excellent, with layers in the middle showing different flavors in the mouth, and finally ending with the bitter taste of coffee. For the first time in my life, I experienced the joy of tasting coffee. Experience (amazing). Highly recommended if you come to Ho Chi Minh City, there are many chain stores so don’t look for this one specifically. The only drawback: I don’t know how to drink coffee when I go back to Taiwan😅😅.

text: This is a coffee shop located near Ben Thanh Market in District 1, Ho Chi Minh City. Perhaps because it is a franchise coffee shop, there are quite a few coffee shops with the same name in downtown Ho Chi Minh City. It's a place that hasn't been around for a long time, so it doesn't appear on the map. We sell various types of coffee, simple bread, coffee beans, etc. If you order on the 1st floor, you will be given a numbered ticket, and if you go up to the 2nd floor and wait, it will be brought to your table. When you order Americano, it is served in a transparent glass, but it has no handle, making drinking it inconvenient. And it's a bit dark. When I order Legend Coffee, I get freshly brewed espresso coffee, a glass of ice, and condensed milk. Pour espresso over ice, add condensed milk, and mix to make sweet and refreshing Vietnamese coffee. However, the price is 170,000 dong and the amount is relatively small. The tables on the second floor are comfortably prepared.

text: A coffee franchise operated by G7 Coffee, a famous coffee company in Vietnam. Along with Highland Coffee and Pungrong(?) Coffee, it is the most visible and has the highest price range. Người vào quán cà phê dường như không phải để uống cà phê đúng nghĩa, nhưng đến vì thói quen, để gặp bạn bè tán gẫu, trao đổi làm ăn, hoặc đến để ngắm nghía các tiếp viên, hoặc cũng có khi chỉ đến để uống vài chai nước ngọt giải khát “vô vị”, “vô hồn”, và sau đó quay lưng ra về mà không một chút do dự. Cà phê bây giờ không như trước đây, đó chỉ là thứ “cà phê kho”, “cà phê tiền chế”, “cà phê đại trà” đã mất vị, mất chất. Do đó, dù quán cà phê có hiện đại, có trang hoàng lộng lẫy đến thế nào đi nữa thì người thưởng thức, nhất là giới trẻ, hay bị chi phối bởi hình thức, ít chú ý đến hương vị đích thực của cà phê. Với nhiều người Việt, cà phê Trung Nguyên vẫn giữ hương vị đậm đà, chất lượng ổn định nhất. Tập đoàn cà phê Trung Nguyên vừa quyết định thay đổi diện mạo chuỗi cà phê của mình. Được đầu tư không gian rộng bao gồm các thư viện sách và còn dành không gian riêng để khách vừa uống cà phê vừa tĩnh tâm và thư giãn, cà phê Trung Nguyên hứa hẹn mang đến một văn hóa cà phê văn minh đúng nghĩa. thank
text: Nowadays, the hobby of drinking coffee has changed a lot, it is no longer like before. People who come to coffee shops don't seem to come to drink coffee in the true sense, but come out of habit, to meet friends to chat, do business, or come to watch the hostesses, or sometimes just come to drank a few bottles of "tasteless", "lifeless" soft drinks, and then turned around and left without the slightest hesitation. Coffee today is not like before, it is just "stored coffee", "pre-processed coffee", "mass coffee" that has lost its taste and quality. Therefore, no matter how modern and splendidly decorated the coffee shop is, people, especially young people, are often influenced by appearance and pay little attention to the true flavor of coffee. . For many Vietnamese people, Trung Nguyen coffee still retains its rich flavor and most stable quality. Trung Nguyen Coffee Group has just decided to change the appearance of its coffee chain. Invested in a large space including book libraries and also dedicated space for customers to drink coffee while calming down and relaxing, Trung Nguyen Coffee promises to bring a truly civilized coffee culture. thank you
